  "rationale": "<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The correct answer is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"30\"><mn>30</mn></math>. It\u2019s given that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x plus y equals 125\"><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>125</mn></math>. Substituting <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"125\"><mn>125</mn></math> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x plus y\"><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>y</mi></math> in the second equation of the given system yields <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"125 plus y equals 155\"><mn>125</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>155</mn></math>. Subtracting <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"125\"><mn>125</mn></math> from both sides of this equation yields <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y equals 30\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>30</mn></math>. Therefore, the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y\"><mi>y</mi></math> is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"30\"><mn>30</mn></math>.</p>",
